Forensic Analysis Engine v0.1.0

Usage: forensic_cli <command> [options]

Commands:
  verify                   Run case verification
  export                   Export case with verification guard
  verify-export            Run verification then export in one step
  replay                   Run case replay (stability test)
  replay-verify            Run replay then verification
  watchpoints              Enable/disable integrity watchpoints
  violations               List integrity violations
  timeline                 List merged case timeline events
  registry-persistence    Correlate registry persistence signals
  execution-correlation   Correlate prefetch/jumplist/shortcut execution traces
  violations-clear        Clear integrity violations
  triage-session          Run full triage session with defensibility bundle
  add-to-notes            Add selection to notes (no typing required)
  presets                 List available examiner presets
  examine                 Run examination with preset
  case                    Case management commands
  capabilities            Show capability registry
  macos-catalog          Parse/list macOS artifact catalog sources
  doctor                  Run diagnostics and health checks
  smoke-test              Run quick validation test on an image
  <image>                  Analyze disk image (default command)

Image Analysis Options:
  --json <file>        Export audit log to JSON file
  --csv <file>         Export audit log to CSV file
  --timeline <file>   Export timeline to CSV file
  --summary <file>    Export summary report to text file
  --mft [count]       Enumerate NTFS MFT records (default: 1000)
  --timeline-console  Show timeline in console (implies --mft)
  --strings           Extract strings from image
  --detect-types      Detect file types by signature
  --carve            Run signature-based carving
  --tree [depth]     Walk NTFS directory tree (default depth: 3)
  --analysis         Show timeline analysis

Verify Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID to verify
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --sample <N>       Sample last N events for hash chain check
  --strict-fts       Fail if FTS queue is not empty
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output

Export Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID to export
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --output <dir>     Output directory (default: ./export_<case_id>)
  --no-verify        Skip verification requirement
  --strict           Fail on warnings
  --max-age <sec>    Maximum age of verification report in seconds

Verify-Export Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --output <dir>     Output directory
  --sample <N>       Sample last N events for verification
  --strict           Fail on warnings
  --max-age <sec>    Maximum age of verification report

Replay Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --sample <N>       Sample N rows per table for fingerprint
  --no-fts          Skip FTS rebuild
  --no-readmodels    Skip read model rebuild
  --optimize         Run database optimize after replay
  --fts-batch <N>    FTS queue batch size
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output

Replay-Verify Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --sample <N>       Sample N rows for verification
  --strict           Fail on verification warnings

Watchpoints Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --enable           Enable integrity watchpoints
  --disable          Disable integrity watchpoints
  --status           Show watchpoint status (default)
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output

Violations Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --since <utc>      Filter violations since UTC timestamp
  --limit <N>        Limit results (default: 50)
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output

Timeline Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --from <utc>       Filter events at/after UTC timestamp
  --to <utc>         Filter events at/before UTC timestamp
  --limit <N>        Limit results (default: 200, max: 2000)
  --source <name>    Source filter: all|activity|evidence|violations
  --json             Print merged timeline payload as JSON
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output

Registry-Persistence Command Options:
  --autorun-reg <path> Path to autorun .reg export (default: exports/autorun.reg)
  --bam-reg <path>     Path to BAM/DAM .reg export (default: exports/bam.reg)
  --amcache-reg <path> Path to Amcache .reg export (default: exports/amcache.reg)
  --tasks-root <path>  Root directory containing task XML files
  --limit <N>          Limit results (default: 200, max: 5000)
  --json               Print command payload as JSON
  --json-result <file> Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet              Suppress console output

Execution-Correlation Command Options:
  --prefetch-dir <path>  Prefetch directory (default: C:\Windows\Prefetch)
  --jumplist-path <path> Jump List source (default: %APPDATA%\Microsoft\Windows\Recent\AutomaticDestinations)
  --shortcuts-base <path> Base user directory for .lnk traversal (default: %USERPROFILE%)
  --limit <N>            Limit results (default: 200, max: 5000)
  --json                 Print command payload as JSON
  --json-result <file>   Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet                Suppress console output

macOS-Catalog Command Options:
  --list             List available macOS catalog artifact keys
  --key <id>         Parse only one artifact key
  --limit <N>        Limit records returned (default: 200, max: 5000)
  --json             Print command payload as JSON
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output

Violations-Clear Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output

Presets Command Options:
  list                List all available examiner presets
  show --name <name> Show details of a specific preset

Examine Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID (required)
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --preset <name>   Preset name (Strict Examiner, Standard Examiner, Fast Triage)
  --override-json <path> JSON file with option overrides
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output
  --help             Show this help message

Case Command Options:
  init                Initialize a new case database
    --case <id>      Case ID (required)
    --db <path>     Path to case database
  set-auto-preset    Set auto-start examination preset
    --case <id>      Case ID (required)
    --db <path>     Path to case database
    --preset <name> Preset name or 'none' to clear

Doctor Command Options:
  --bundle <dir>     Generate diagnostics bundle
  --verbose          Verbose output

Smoke-Test Command Options:
  --image <path>      Path to image file (required)
  --out <dir>         Output directory (default: .\exports\smoke_test)
  --mft <count>       MFT record count (default: 50)
  --no-timeline       Skip timeline CSV generation
  --no-audit         Skip audit JSON generation
  --quiet             Only print final one-line status
  --json-summary <path> Path for summary JSON (default: <out>\smoke_summary.json)

Triage-Session Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID (required)
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --name <name>      Session name (optional)
  --no-watchpoints   Disable integrity watchpoints
  --no-replay       Skip replay step
  --no-verify       Skip verify step
  --strict           Fail on warnings and violations
  --bundle-dir <dir> Bundle output directory (default: exports/defensibility)
  --no-bundle       Skip bundle export
  --sample <N>       Sample size for replay/verify
  --json-result <file>  Write JSON result envelope to file
  --quiet            Suppress console output
  --help             Show this help message

Add-to-Notes Command Options:
  --case <id>        Case ID (required)
  --db <path>        Path to case database
  --mode <mode>      Mode: note, exhibits, packet (default: note)
  --from-json <path> JSON file with SelectionContext + items (required)
  --screenshot <path> Optional screenshot path to link
  --tag <tag>        Tag to add (can be repeated)
  --explain           Run explain on created exhibits
  --max-items <N>     Maximum items (default: 200)
  --help             Show this help message

Examples:
  forensic_cli disk.img --json audit.json --summary report.txt --mft 5000
  forensic_cli verify --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite
  forensic_cli export --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite
  forensic_cli verify-export --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite
  forensic_cli replay --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite
  forensic_cli replay-verify --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite
  forensic_cli watchpoints --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite --enable
  forensic_cli violations --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite
  forensic_cli timeline --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite --limit 200 --json
  forensic_cli registry-persistence --autorun-reg ./exports/autorun.reg --bam-reg ./exports/bam.reg --json
  forensic_cli registry-persistence --autorun-reg ./exports/autorun.reg --bam-reg ./exports/bam.reg --amcache-reg ./exports/amcache.reg --json
  forensic_cli execution-correlation --prefetch-dir C:\Windows\Prefetch --json
  forensic_cli macos-catalog --list --json
  forensic_cli add-to-notes --case case123 --db ./cases/case123.sqlite --mode exhibits --from-json selection.json
  forensic_cli doctor --verbose
